transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I just got charged for another order of Score Blue, but I never even received my first order.

Speaker 1: What's your last name?

Speaker 2: Williams.

Speaker 1: And your zip code, Mr. Williams?

Speaker 2: Eight seven one zero eight.

Speaker 1: What's the first name?

Speaker 2: Terry.

Speaker 1: All righty. Oh.

Speaker 2: Wow, yeah, I do see that here.

Speaker 1: You—

Speaker 2: Give me just a second, okay?

Speaker 1: You—

Speaker 2: The first order came back to us. I'm not sure why.

Speaker 1: So, I mean, did you want—did you want to get one of these orders, right?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I wanted the first order and then I just looked and they just charged me for a second order. I didn't even, you know—

Speaker 1: Yeah, the second order—

Speaker 2: It's weird too because it wasn't even 30 days later. It was like 35 days later.

Speaker 1: Usually, like when they set you up on that VIP prescription thing, it's like 30, 60, 90 days later, but there's 35.

Speaker 2: I think it might have been a little glitch in the system. What I can do for you, Mr—

Speaker 1: Williams is I can pause this account for up to six months for you.

Speaker 2: Give you some time to try these pills out when we actually are able to get them to you.

Speaker 1: I see here on FedEx it says it was returned to sender.

Speaker 2: So yeah, I can cancel that order out for you. Don't want the second one.

Speaker 1: You want me to cancel? I want to refund it for you.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 2: So I'll go ahead and do that and then the first order started that, so don't worry about that.

Speaker 1: That was not gonna come. You're gonna see it refunded to your card.

Speaker 2: The second or the first order? I just don't know why I didn't get there though. Are you at—what's your address?

Speaker 1: 1-1-12 Nevada Drive Northeast.

Speaker 2: They're like a letter C?

Speaker 1: Yeah, apartment C.

Speaker 2: Albuquerque, New Mexico 87108.

Speaker 1: Yes. Yes. I definitely—I'm gonna reship this to you. I'll get the overnight to you again as well.

Speaker 2: I don't know why I didn't get there though.

Speaker 1: It says you're unable to deliver shipment, but it doesn't have a reason why. It says delivery exception.

Speaker 2: You can be received. I didn't even get a note or nothing.

Speaker 1: I mean, I don't know if I can give you the gate number or do I have to give it to FedEx?

Speaker 2: This FedEx, I mean, they should already know. I feel like the gate number, right?

Speaker 1: I do love, like, an apartment complex.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so I'm sure people are getting FedEx delivery, so you would think they would have access to get into the complex, you know.

Speaker 1: Right, yeah.

Speaker 2: So, I mean, I definitely—I'm gonna reship this to you. It's up to you.

Speaker 1: Do you want me to send this FedEx or do you want me to send this USPS? Whatever you think is safest.

Speaker 2: Um, USPS. I know, I know the mailman has—

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay, perfect. So yeah, I'm gonna go ahead. I'm gonna take care of that for you.

Speaker 1: I'm gonna reship this order and then I'll pause this account for you.

Speaker 2: So you have some time to try the pills but like nothing else will come out.

Speaker 1: Just give us a call back before July once you get a chance to try these. You'll see this order, Mr. Williams, come before—

Speaker 2: It'll show up before this upcoming Friday or by this Friday latest, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you, man. I really appreciate that.

Speaker 2: Yeah, no problem.

Speaker 1: No problem and you're all set. Okay, let us know how it goes.

Speaker 2: All right. Thank you. Thank you. Bye. Have a good day.
